~","text_ar":"خَزّ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bordered"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muEolamap","text_ar":"مُعْلَمَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"); not unless bordered: so called because of its softness and thinness, and smallness of bulk when it is folded: Ahmad Ibn-Fáris says that it is the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"black"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kisaA='","text_ar":"كِسَا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":": and he says that it may be thus called because a man wraps himself with it, so that it is against his"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axomaS","text_ar":"اَخْمَص"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning by this his waist: (Har p. 21:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xamaAy^iSu","text_ar":"خَمَايِصُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xmAy^S","text_ar":"خمايص"},{"kind":"text","text":"are"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"garments of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaz~","text_ar":"خَزّ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thick, black,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"red, and having thick"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEolaAm","text_ar":"اَعْلَام"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"borders such as above described"},{"kind":"text","text":"];"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"worn by people of old."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) El-Aashà says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"A_i*aA jur~idato yawomFA Hasibota xamiySapF\n                      \n                     \n                        EalayohaA wa jiroyaAla Aln~aDiyri Ald~ulaAmiSaA"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"When she is stripped of her clothing, any day, thou wouldst think there was upon her a khameesah, and the glistening redness of gold"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: As says, he likens her [long and spreading] hair to a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xmySp","text_ar":"خميصة"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is black. (S.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","tex